{
  "texts": [
    "They have 384 × 384 pixels in an image area of 28.8 mm × 28.8 mm, yielding a square field of view of 1.",
    "Each pixel corresponds to a sky area of 9.",
    "The nominal integration time for all eROSITA CCDs is 50 msec.",
    "The additional presence of a frame-store area in the CCD reduces substantially the amount of so-called out-of-time events, which are recorded during the CCD read-out, a significant improvement with respect to the EPIC-pn camera on XMM-Newton.",
    "For optimal performance during operations, the CCDs are cooled down to about -85 • by means of passive elements (Fürmetz et al. 2008)."
  ]
}